# 04WT2 – Label Studio Setup & Protein Dataset Creation
**Project:** Deep Learning-Based Visual Analytics of Molecular Dynamics Trajectories
**Detection Classes:** alpha_helix, beta_sheet
**Week:** 4 | **Task:** 2

---

## Objective

Install Label Studio in a dedicated virtual environment, load VMD-rendered protein
trajectory frames, annotate alpha-helices and beta-sheets with bounding boxes,
and export a complete YOLO-format dataset.

---

## Step 1: Install Label Studio (Separate Virtual Environment)

```bash
# Create a dedicated environment — NOT inside ultralytics
python -m venv ~/envs/labelstudio_env
source ~/envs/labelstudio_env/bin/activate   # Linux/Mac
# or: ~/envs/labelstudio_env/Scripts/activate  (Windows)

pip install label-studio

# Launch
label-studio start
# Opens at: http://localhost:8080
```

> ⚠️ **Critical:** Do NOT install Label Studio inside the Ultralytics environment.
> They have conflicting dependencies. Always use a separate virtual environment.

---

## Step 2: Render Protein Video in VMD & Extract Frames

### Render in VMD (NewCartoon + Structure coloring)

```tcl
# VMD Tk Console
mol new 1VII.pdb                  ;# Villin headpiece — clear alpha-helices
mol addfile trajectory.dcd
mol modstyle 0 0 NewCartoon
mol modcolor 0 0 Structure        ;# helix=RED, sheet=YELLOW, coil=WHITE
color Display Background black

# Export all frames
set n [molinfo 0 get numframes]
for {set i 0} {$i < $n} {incr i} {
    molinfo 0 set frame $i
    render TachyonInternal frame_[format "%04d" $i].png
}
```

### Extract frames from rendered video (alternative)

```bash
# If VMD exported a video file
ffmpeg -i protein_trajectory.mp4 -vf fps=10 all_frames/frame_%04d.png
echo "Total frames: $(ls all_frames/ | wc -l)"
# Expected: ~600 from a 60-second render
```

---

## Step 3: Select & Organize Frames

```bash
mkdir -p dataset/{train,val,test}/images

# Train: 100 frames — spaced every ~6 frames for temporal diversity
python3 << 'EOF'
import os, shutil, glob

frames = sorted(glob.glob("all_frames/frame_*.png"))
train_frames = frames[::6][:100]
val_frames   = [f for f in frames[::6] if f not in train_frames][::3][:40]

for f in train_frames:
    shutil.copy(f, f"dataset/train/images/{os.path.basename(f)}")
for f in val_frames:
    shutil.copy(f, f"dataset/val/images/{os.path.basename(f)}")

print(f"Train: {len(train_frames)} | Val: {len(val_frames)}")
EOF
```

